  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6843.65 trading above the flip strike (6837) in PIN regime, dealers are currently selling delta into strength as they hedge their long gamma positions. The massive positive GEX wall at 6850 (+74.5B) creates a significant magnetic effect just 6 handles away, where dealer selling pressure will intensify on any push higher. The 32.1% GEX surge indicates rapidly increasing dealer hedging activity, reinforcing the mean-reverting dynamics that should keep price action compressed between the 6830 support (max negative gamma) and 6850 resistance zones.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pulled toward 6850 with strong resistance there, creating a tight trading range.",
